segment.source: This reference topic for the IT professional describes the special identity groups (which are sometimes referred to as security groups) that are used in Windows access control.
segment.target: This reference topic for the IT professional describes the special identity groups (which are sometimes referred to as security groups) that are used in Windows access control.

segment.source: Special identity groups are similar to Active Directory security groups as listed in the users and built-in containers.
segment.target: Special identity groups are similar to Active Directory security groups as listed in the users and built-in containers.

segment.source: Special identity groups can provide an efficient way to assign access to resources in your network.
segment.target: Special identity groups can provide an efficient way to assign access to resources in your network.

segment.source: By using special identity groups, you can:
segment.target: By using special identity groups, you can:

segment.source: Assign user rights to security groups in Active Directory.
segment.target: Assign user rights to security groups in Active Directory.

segment.source: Assign permissions to security groups for the purpose of accessing resources.
segment.target: Assign permissions to security groups for the purpose of accessing resources.

segment.source: Servers that are running the supported Windows Server operating systems designated in the Applies To list at the beginning of this topic include several special identity groups.
segment.target: Servers that are running the supported Windows Server operating systems designated in the Applies To list at the beginning of this topic include several special identity groups.

segment.source: These special identity groups do not have specific memberships that can be modified, but they can represent different users at different times, depending on the circumstances.
segment.target: These special identity groups do not have specific memberships that can be modified, but they can represent different users at different times, depending on the circumstances.

segment.source: Although the special identity groups can be assigned rights and permissions to resources, the memberships cannot be modified or viewed.
segment.target: Although the special identity groups can be assigned rights and permissions to resources, the memberships cannot be modified or viewed.

segment.source: Group scopes do not apply to special identity groups.
segment.target: Group scopes do not apply to special identity groups.

segment.source: Users are automatically assigned to these special identity groups whenever they sign in or access a particular resource.
segment.target: Users are automatically assigned to these special identity groups whenever they sign in or access a particular resource.

segment.source: For information about security groups and group scope, see Active Directory Security Groups.
segment.target: For information about security groups and group scope, see Active Directory Security Groups.

segment.source: The special identity groups are described in the following tables.
segment.target: The special identity groups are described in the following tables.

segment.source: Any user who accesses the system through an anonymous logon has the Anonymous Logon identity.
segment.target: Any user who accesses the system through an anonymous logon has the Anonymous Logon identity.

segment.source: This identity allows anonymous access to resources, such as a web page that is published on corporate servers.
segment.target: This identity allows anonymous access to resources, such as a web page that is published on corporate servers.

segment.source: The Anonymous Logon group is not a member of the Everyone group by default.
segment.target: The Anonymous Logon group is not a member of the Everyone group by default.

segment.source: Any user who accesses the system through a sign-in process has the Authenticated Users identity.
segment.target: Any user who accesses the system through a sign-in process has the Authenticated Users identity.

segment.source: This identity allows access to shared resources within the domain, such as files in a shared folder that should be accessible to all the workers in the organization.
segment.target: This identity allows access to shared resources within the domain, such as files in a shared folder that should be accessible to all the workers in the organization.
